text_1_2= "QuickLOAD uses the following interior ballistics principles for predictive calculations:"
text_1_3= ""
text_1_4= "Mainly, QuickLOAD accomplishes interior ballistics calculation through incorporation of a mathematical model of"
text_1_5= "smokeless powder burning characteristics (as appropriate to the specific powder). This model accounts for most"
text_1_6= "variations resulting from differences in granule shape, chemistry, surface treatment and layer treatment."
text_1_7= "QuickLOAD accomplishes a good approximation of propellant combustion through the appropriate conjunction of two"
text_1_8= "parabolic curves. The first curve simulates the progressive portion of granule burning (increasing burning rate)."
text_1_9= "The second curve approximates the degressive portion of granule burning (decreasing burning rate)."
text_1_10= "QuickLOAD computes the firing sequence through a system of interior ballistic approximation formulas. These"
text_1_11= "include: propellant combustion (burning function), projectile motion equations and energy balance equations. "
text_1_12= ""
text_1_13= "QuickLOAD characterizes internal ballistic energy losses through a weighting factor (friction and heat). This factor adds"
text_1_14= "a portion of the propellant charge to the moving mass (projectile including sabot). A separate long barrel function can also"
text_1_15= "account for barrel friction, in those rare situations when bullet-to-bore friction becomes a significant portion of bullet"
text_1_16= "base pressure (only noted in unusally long barrels). "
text_1_17= "QuickLOAD represents bullet start friction (bullet-to-case friction, rifling engravement forces) through an initial"
text_1_18= "offset- or Shot-Start pressure value."
text_1_19= "The user can temporarily or permanently change the popellant properties and all other data"
text_1_20= "in QuickLOAD's database."
text_1_21= "QuickLOAD allows any meaningful internal ballistic calculation and all modifications that might be necessary to"
text_1_22= "accomodate such results, whether feasible or imaginary."
text_1_23= "The author recommends the book ''Theory of the Interior Ballistics of Guns'', Wiley & Sons, New York,"
text_1_24= "by J. Corner. This source offers significant information on interior ballistics theory."
text_1_25= "The author also suggests ''Metallic Cartridge Reloading'', DBI-Books, Inc., by M.L. McPherson,"
text_1_26= "ISBN 0-87349-180-7, a great source for handloading data and instructions."
text_1_27= "Hartmut G. Broemel,  64832 Babenhausen / Germany"

text_2_3= "QuickLOAD - Interior Ballistics Predictor Program|true,False,False,204"
text_2_4= "Based upon a theoretical model and not on empirical data from any tests.|true,False,TRUE,204"
text_2_5= "D I S C L A I M E R|true,False,FALSE,204"
text_2_6= "This software is licensed >AS IS< and is offered without any warranties as to performance or merchantability.|true,False,TRUE,204"
text_2_7= "Our entire liability shall be, at our option, either to return purchase price or replace software. Since we have no control over components"
text_2_8= "and equipment that might be used with this software, we neither assume nor imply any responsibilities for any results the user might"
text_2_9= "obtain. To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, in no event shall the seller, manufacturer or agent of same be liable for any"
text_2_10= "damages whatsoever (including, without limitation, direct or indirect damages, personal injury or death, business losses, or any other"
text_2_11= "pecuniary loss) ensuing out of licensees's use or inability to use this software. We strongly advise user to thoroughly test this program"
text_2_12= "before relying upon any results. The user must assume the entire risk of using this program and any data generated for any purpose."
text_2_13= "Ballistic programs such as QuickLOAD cannot predict EXACT internal ballistic results. Therefore one|true,False,true,204"
text_2_14= "CANNOT use this software as a substitute for information gleaned from a reloading manual along with standard|true,False,true,204"
text_2_15= "handload development and practices. QuickLOAD is designed and intended only for use by those persons who|true,False,true,204"
text_2_16= "are completely familiar with all safe handloading practices. It is mandatory to verify any computer-generated|true,False,true,204"
text_2_17= "results with data found in current manuals. NEVER use charges exceeding recommended maximum charges|true,False,true,204"
text_2_18= "or reduce charges below recommended minimum (start) charges as representing in such modern manuals.|true,False,true,204"
text_2_19= "This program assumes use of the mildest primer that will do the job in the specified load."
text_2_20= "Primer substitutions can raise chamber pressures to unsafe levels; equally, bullet substitutions often result in"
text_2_21= "significant chamber pressure differences. Much of the data shipped with this program (particularly propellant"
text_2_22= "data) contains approximated values. These values can or will become obsolete every time a manufacturer"
text_2_23= "introduces a new production or manufacturing process. This will result in erroneous calculated data for both"
text_2_24= "pressure and velocity. Similarly, component production tolerances will alter actual results. Handload results"
text_2_25= "will also vary, depending upon conditions that this software does not explicitly consider or take into account."
text_2_26= "UNSAFE HANDLOADING PRACTICES AND USE OF ANY RESULTING AMMUNITION CAN RESULT IN|true,False,true,204"
text_2_27= "PROPERTY DAMAGE AND PERSONAL INJURY OR DEATH TO HANDLOADER, SHOOTER OR BYSTANDERS.|true,False,true,204"
text_2_28= "Warning: Copyright laws and international treaties protect this software. Unauthorized reproduction or reverse engineering"
text_2_29= "of this program, or any portion thereof, can result in severe civil and criminal penalties."
text_2_30= "If you do not understand the above information or you do not agree to the above-specified terms, exit this|true,False,true,204"
text_2_31= "программы сейчас же, нажав на кнопку Выйти, расположенную ниже!|true,False,true,204"

